'''Jaloliddin Qadomboy oʻgʻli Masharipov''' (born 1 September 1993) is an Uzbek professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Winger (association football)|winger]] for [[Persian Gulf Pro League]] club [[Esteghlal F.C.|Esteghlal]], and the [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan national team]].

==Club career==
In July 2020, it was reported that he was linked to [[Süper Lig]] team [[Trabzonspor]]. He later played a key role in [[2020 Pakhtakor Tashkent FK season|Pakhtakor's 2020 season]], scoring nine goals and had 22 assists in 35 appearances in all competitions. However, his early exit after receiving a red card had a major role in his team's loss against [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] in the [[2020 AFC Champions League knockout stage#West Region 2|2020 AFC Champions League quarter-finals]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Persepolis see off Pakhtakor to book AFC Champions League semi-final berth |url=https://www.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-champions-league/latest/news/persepolis-see-off-pakhtakor-to-book-afc-champions-league-semi-final-berth |website=the-AFC}}</ref>

On 26 December 2020, he signed for Saudi club [[Al Nassr FC|Al Nassr]].<ref>{{cite web |title=الأوزبكي "ماشاريبوف" يؤكد توقيعه لـ"النصر" |url=https://sabq.org/S8nbPc |website=صحيفة سبق الإلكترونية |date=26 December 2020 |language=ar}}</ref> Next month, Masharipov was sent on loan to Emirati club [[Shabab Al-Ahli Club|Shabab Al-Ahli]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Uzbekistan star Masharipov loaned to Shabab Al Ahli after Al Nassr switch |url=https://www.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-champions-league/latest/news/uzbekistan-star-masharipov-loaned-to-shabab-al-ahli-after-al-nassr-switch |website=the-AFC}}</ref>

After returning from his loan spell, he wore the number 7 jersey for Al Nassr. In January 2023, when [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] signed for the Saudi club, Masharipov changed to number 77, allowing the Portuguese star to wear his iconic number 7.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Lewis |first=Kyle |date=9 February 2023 |title='Why I gave Ronaldo my No. 7 shirt at Al Nassr' |url=https://www.snl24.com/kickoff/worldnews/cristiano-ronaldos-teammate-jaloliddin-masharipov-why-i-gave-him-my-no-7-shirt-at-al-nassr-20230209 |access-date=2023-09-27 |website=KickOff |language=en-US}}</ref>

On 17 August 2023, Al Nassr announced that Masharipov's contract had been terminated by mutual agreement.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-08-17 |title=Al Nassr anuncia rescisão e abre mais uma vaga de estrangeiro |trans-title=Al Nassr announces termination and opens another foreign vacancy |url=https://www.ojogo.pt/internacional/noticias/al-nassr-anuncia-rescisao-e-abre-mais-uma-vaga-de-estrangeiro-16874622.html |access-date=2023-09-27 |publisher=O Jogo |language=pt-PT}}</ref>

On 27 September 2023, Masharipov signed a one-year deal with [[Super League Greece]] club [[Panserraikos F.C.|Panserraikos]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=2023-09-27 |title=O Jaloliddin Masharipov στον Πανσερραϊκό! |trans-title=Jaloliddin Masharipov in Panserraikos! |url=https://panserraikosfc.gr/o-jaloliddin-masharipov-%CF%83%CF%84%CE%BF%CE%BD-%CF%80%CE%B1%CE%BD%CF%83%CE%B5%CF%81%CF%81%CE%B1%CF%8A%CE%BA%CF%8C/ |access-date= |website=Panserraikos FC |language=el}}</ref> On 31 January 2024, Panserraikos announced the departure of Masharipov.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ευχαριστούμε "Μάσα"! |url=https://panserraikosfc.gr/%ce%b5%cf%85%cf%87%ce%b1%cf%81%ce%b9%cf%83%cf%84%ce%bf%cf%8d%ce%bc%ce%b5-%ce%bc%ce%ac%cf%83%ce%b1/ |website=panserraikosfc.gr |publisher=Panserraikos F.C. |access-date=1 February 2024 |language=Greek |date=31 January 2024}}</ref>

== International career ==
[[File:TUR-UZB 20190113 Asian Cup 6.jpg|thumb| Jaloliddin Masharipov handshake with [[Zafar Babajanow]] before the match Turkmenistan vs. Uzbekistan at the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]].]] 
Masharipov played for [[Uzbekistan national under-20 football team|Uzbekistan U-20]] since 2013. He was also called up in 2015 for the [[King's Cup (Thailand football tournament)|King's Cup]] in Thailand, but he received a red card in the first half after launching a flying, studs-up kick into the chest of South Korea's [[Kang Sang-woo]]. Later he was also called up for senior team and Masharipov made his first appearance in national team on 6 October 2016, replacing [[Sardor Rashidov]] as substitute in the 61st minute, in a 0–1 loss [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (AFC)|2018 World Cup qualifier]] game against [[Iran national football team|Iran]].<ref name="NFT">{{NFT|64895}}</ref>

